==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Problematical
<hw>Prob`lem*at"ic*al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>problematicus</ets>,
Gr. <?/: cf. F. <ets>probl⟦eacute⟧matique</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Having the nature of a problem; not shown in fact; questionable;
uncertain; unsettled; doubtful; <as>as, his theory is
<ex>problematic</ex> because it fails to explain several
facts</as>.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Prob`lem*at"ic*al*ly</wf>,
<pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Diligent inquiries into remote and <qex>problematical</qex> guilt
leave a gate wide open to . . . informers.</q>
<rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Having characteristics which will create
difficulties or undesirable consequences; -- of a proposed action;
<as>as, the proposed law is <ex>problematic</ex> because it will cause
many people to lose their jobs</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Problematist</ent>⟦br⟧
